\index{save() (méthode main.models.AnneeUniversitaire)@\spxentry{save()}\spxextra{méthode main.models.AnneeUniversitaire}}

\begin{fulllineitems}

\sphinxAtStartPar
Save the current instance. Override this in a subclass if you want to
control the saving process.

\sphinxAtStartPar
The “force\_insert” and “force\_update” parameters can be used to insist
that the « save » must be an SQL insert or update (or equivalent for
non\sphinxhyphen{}SQL backends), respectively. Normally, they should not be set.

\index{save() (méthode main.models.Charge)@\spxentry{save()}\spxextra{méthode main.models.Charge}}

\begin{fulllineitems}
\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{main/model:main.models.Charge.save}}
\pysigstartsignatures
\pysiglinewithargsret{\sphinxbfcode{\sphinxupquote{save}}}{\sphinxparam{\DUrole{o}{*}\DUrole{n}{args}}\sphinxparamcomma \sphinxparam{\DUrole{o}{**}\DUrole{n}{kwargs}}}{}
\pysigstopsignatures
\sphinxAtStartPar
Save the current instance. Override this in a subclass if you want to
control the saving process.

\sphinxAtStartPar
The “force\_insert” and “force\_update” parameters can be used to insist
that the « save » must be an SQL insert or update (or equivalent for
non\sphinxhyphen{}SQL backends), respectively. Normally, they should not be set.

\end{fulllineitems}

\begin{fulllineitems}
\phantomsection\label{\detokenize{main/model:main.models.Comptable.save}}
\pysigstartsignatures
\pysiglinewithargsret{\sphinxbfcode{\sphinxupquote{save}}}{\sphinxparam{\DUrole{n}{force\_insert}\DUrole{o}{=}\DUrole{default_value}{False}}\sphinxparamcomma \sphinxparam{\DUrole{n}{force\_update}\DUrole{o}{=}\DUrole{default_value}{False}}\sphinxparamcomma \sphinxparam{\DUrole{n}{using}\DUrole{o}{=}\DUrole{default_value}{None}}}{}
\pysigstopsignatures
\sphinxAtStartPar
Save the current instance. Override this in a subclass if you want to
control the saving process.

\sphinxAtStartPar
The “force\_insert” and “force\_update” parameters can be used to insist
that the « save » must be an SQL insert or update (or equivalent for
non\sphinxhyphen{}SQL backends), respectively. Normally, they should not be set.

\index{save() (méthode main.models.Evaluation)@\spxentry{save()}\spxextra{méthode main.models.Evaluation}}

\pysigstopsignatures
\sphinxAtStartPar
Save the current instance. Override this in a subclass if you want to
control the saving process.

\sphinxAtStartPar
The “force\_insert” and “force\_update” parameters can be used to insist
that the « save » must be an SQL insert or update (or equivalent for
non\sphinxhyphen{}SQL backends), respectively. Normally, they should not be set.

non\sphinxhyphen{}SQL backends), respectively. Normally, they should not be set.

Save the current instance. Override this in a subclass if you want to
control the saving process.

\sphinxAtStartPar
The “force\_insert” and “force\_update” parameters can be used to insist
that the « save » must be an SQL insert or update (or equivalent for
non\sphinxhyphen{}SQL backends), respectively. Normally, they should not be set.

\pysigstopsignatures
\sphinxAtStartPar
Save the current instance. Override this in a subclass if you want to
control the saving process.

\sphinxAtStartPar
The “force\_insert” and “force\_update” parameters can be used to insist
that the « save » must be an SQL insert or update (or equivalent for
non\sphinxhyphen{}SQL backends), respectively. Normally, they should not be set.
